cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CC 

This paper deals with network recovery from link failures, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses coding techniques, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes an algorithm for network design, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also evaluates the performance of the proposed technique in terms of Quality of Recovery (QoR), which could be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
